  <name>comprimé</name>
  <summary>Compress and re-encode video files</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      comprimé re-encodes video files with ffmpeg to produce smaller, widely
      compatible H.264/AAC MP4 files. Open one or several videos at once, pick a
      quality level, and comprimé writes a re-encoded copy next to each original.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Batch re-encoding of multiple files</li>
      <li>Quality presets from default (CRF) to extra low bitrate</li>
      <li>Per-file progress</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
  <launchable type="desktop-id">fr.benjaminbellamy.comprime.desktop</launchable>
